<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-706-828  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 706 828.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Sept 25 1989 v23 n39 p65(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Shhh! Don't talk tech at Cadbury. (Cadbury Schweppe's innovativeinformation systems management technique)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pastore, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Cadbury Schweppes USA CIO Joe Nash is responsible for aninnovative management technique for the company's MIS department.andO;The technique, called a 'business review,' helps Cadbury bring itsmany acquisitions together with a minimum of technical problems.andO;MIS staff actually go into the field, learn how the businessmanagers do their jobs and may actually make calls with thesalespeople.andP;  During the initial review, the MIS people are notallowed to mention technology.andP;  Only after the review do they sitdown and determine where automation may help.andP;  Cadbury ports itsvarious acquisitions' financial application to an IBM 3081 Model Kand converts all internal applications to standardized packagesrunning in IBM MVS and PC environments.andP;  The business review mayalso determine the standard packages, or even automationaltogether, is inappropriate for certain applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cadbury Schweppes U.S.A. Inc. (management).andO;Topic:     MISManagement of EDPAutomationBeverage IndustryExecutive.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Joe Nash. (portrait)Person:    Nash, Joe (management).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>